WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.446
TOMMY: <i>Remember last night
when you asked after Mama?</i>

00:03.520 --> 00:04.931
(GUNSHOT)

00:08.680 --> 00:11.570
<i>LXNDA". Do they always have to do
the stock taking at night, Arthur?</i>

00:11.640 --> 00:12.801
I'm gonna have a baby.

00:12.880 --> 00:13.881
(CHUCKLES)

00:14.280 --> 00:16.726
What business do you have
with the Russians, Tommy?

00:16.800 --> 00:18.040
<i>TOMMY". I've been to the factories</i>

00:18.120 --> 00:19.929
<i>and the armoured vehicles
are in good condition.</i>

00:20.080 --> 00:22.845
"A factory break-in,"
that's what you said.

00:22.920 --> 00:24.160
HUGHES: When you go home today,

00:24.240 --> 00:26.083
be sure to check
under your little boy's pillow.

00:27.280 --> 00:28.645
<i>We can reach anyone.</i>

00:29.320 --> 00:30.321
<i>Anywhere.</i>

00:31.360 --> 00:33.840
TOMMY: <i>The priest is passing
information about the robbery</i>

00:33.920 --> 00:35.729
<i>to a Lloyds underwriter called Monkland.</i>

00:35.800 --> 00:38.326
TATIANA: Why would the priest
pass information to our enemies?

00:38.760 --> 00:40.808
<i>TOMMY".
The complexities are your business.</i>

00:41.040 --> 00:45.284
Now give me permission
to kill the priest.

00:59.520 --> 01:00.646
(GUNSHOT)

01:01.560 --> 01:03.562
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:56.560 --> 01:58.403
ARTHUR: Watch out, john-Boy,
he has got a strong left.

01:58.480 --> 02:01.563
- TOMMY: Arthur,john, Finn. Come here.
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:02.680 --> 02:04.170
(HORSE NEIGHS)

02:08.520 --> 02:10.249
ARTHUR: All right, what is it?

02:15.800 --> 02:19.202
This letter says that Dad's dead.

02:26.640 --> 02:29.928
He was in Boston
in a bar called the Mickey Free.

02:30.600 --> 02:33.001
Two men waiting in an alley.
He was shot twice.

02:36.000 --> 02:37.684
Who's Rosie Rice?

02:39.320 --> 02:40.685
Some fucking whore.

02:40.760 --> 02:43.764
She is a woman
who took the trouble to write to us.

02:44.160 --> 02:46.845
And she wanted us to know
that during the night,

02:47.680 --> 02:50.650
while he was dying,
he asked for our forgiveness.

02:53.400 --> 02:57.325
The only thing he ever taught us
was how to kill and cut a stag.

02:57.720 --> 03:01.930
- Finn, john, you won't remember.
- I remember. Cannock Chase.

03:03.280 --> 03:05.681
Parked up at a pub called the Griffin.

03:06.120 --> 03:09.090
He got drunk and sang Silver <i>Dagger</i>
about 100 times.

03:09.160 --> 03:10.605
Yeah. One weekend.

03:11.880 --> 03:13.882
One weekend he was like that.

03:15.800 --> 03:17.928
TOMMY: The stag is to remember him.

03:18.720 --> 03:21.371
We eat and then we forget him.

03:22.720 --> 03:24.848
No need to forgive him. Agreed?

03:29.600 --> 03:31.967
John, I have to say this.

03:32.040 --> 03:34.520
You can name your new baby after him
if you like.

03:34.600 --> 03:35.726
No.

03:36.640 --> 03:38.449
Arthur, I won't even ask.

03:41.640 --> 03:43.130
So his name dies.

03:43.840 --> 03:46.764
It's been in the family for a long time,
but now it's gone.

03:48.640 --> 03:51.166
All right, that's done. Fuck him.

03:53.080 --> 03:56.004
Before we cook and eat,
there's some business.

03:56.080 --> 03:57.081
Boys!

04:08.480 --> 04:12.690
I wanted to say this out here, 'cause
I don't trust the maids in the house.

04:14.920 --> 04:16.524
There's gonna be a robbery.

04:26.480 --> 04:29.450
- I wish to confess.
- There's no confessional today.

04:29.520 --> 04:30.965
The name's Shelby.

04:45.280 --> 04:47.362
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

04:47.680 --> 04:49.364
Today is a holy day.

04:49.440 --> 04:52.887
Look, I came. I made myself.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.081
Have you been drinking?

04:56.160 --> 04:57.400
I couldn't sleep.

04:59.880 --> 05:02.770
I tried to get enough down me
to get myself to sleep, but...

05:04.760 --> 05:07.969
I just do these night vigils
by myself, thinking...

05:08.640 --> 05:10.642
How long since your last confession?

05:13.600 --> 05:14.965
I don't remember.

05:15.960 --> 05:19.328
Mrs Shelby,
do you have something to confess?

05:19.400 --> 05:24.042
Do you know it is actually "Gray"?
My name is Elizabeth Gray.

05:25.200 --> 05:28.044
Yeah. Do you think God calls me
Pol or Polly?

05:30.960 --> 05:32.769
The voice calls me Pol.

05:34.880 --> 05:36.530
You hear a voice?

05:38.400 --> 05:42.689
- Yeah. Like Bernadette heard a voice.
- And what does the voice say?

05:44.880 --> 05:46.166
"Murderer."

05:50.240 --> 05:52.049
It says this to you?

05:53.760 --> 05:56.331
It's in my head.
Who else would it be talking to?

05:57.720 --> 06:01.008
And are you a murderer?

06:01.960 --> 06:04.531
If you're talking about the law, then...

06:04.600 --> 06:06.364
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

06:07.000 --> 06:08.604
- Yes.
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

06:08.680 --> 06:11.604
- I'll be out in a moment, Peter.
- PETER: Yes, Father.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.730
(FOOTSTEPS FADING)

06:16.200 --> 06:20.330
Are you saying
you want to confess to a murder?

06:21.720 --> 06:22.767
POLLY: No.

06:24.280 --> 06:27.090
My confession is that I feel no regret.

06:28.160 --> 06:33.291
He was a policeman.
He was a bad man. He hurt me.

06:36.760 --> 06:40.242
I do the things I do
so that my son doesn't have to do them.

06:42.280 --> 06:45.204
It's just the wiping away of the shit
from under your feet.

06:45.280 --> 06:48.250
The taking of any human life
is a mortal sin.

06:48.320 --> 06:53.008
No, the unjust taking of a human life
is a mortalsin.

06:53.400 --> 06:55.129
Look it up. Look who did it.

06:55.200 --> 06:57.965
Moses, Samson, Lord Kitchener.

06:58.520 --> 07:02.161
Are you saying
you took the life of a policeman?

07:02.560 --> 07:03.800
(POLLY SIGHS)

07:07.480 --> 07:08.686
(CREAKING)

07:10.320 --> 07:11.526
Oh, Father.

07:14.520 --> 07:16.761
(SOBBING)
Now there is another life to be taken.

07:17.040 --> 07:22.843
If there is a voice telling you
to take a life, you must ignore it.

07:22.920 --> 07:26.163
The voice doesn't tell me.
The voice asks me.

07:26.240 --> 07:28.208
It says, "Pol,

07:28.800 --> 07:31.531
"does this way of excusing
a murder still work

07:32.080 --> 07:37.610
"if the life that is going to be taken
is a consecrated man?"

07:39.320 --> 07:40.970
He's a man of the cloth.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.524
He's a holy man.

07:44.760 --> 07:46.171
What kind of holy man?

07:47.200 --> 07:48.440
(SIGHS)

07:54.000 --> 07:55.286
(DOOR OPENS)

07:56.240 --> 07:57.924
(FOOTSTEPS FADING)

08:04.840 --> 08:06.046
(DOOR CLOSES)

08:07.880 --> 08:09.166
- ESME: It's not fair.
-(DOOR OPENS)

08:09.440 --> 08:12.762
They're off drinking and shooting rifles
as we sit here.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.808
-(DOOR CLOSES)
- Listen to the mugs swearing,

08:14.880 --> 08:18.646
spitting on the bloody floor
for us to fucking wipe up!

08:19.960 --> 08:23.248
Without men here,
they'd be like dogs pissing up the wall.

08:23.840 --> 08:26.002
I was just saying it's not fair.

08:27.000 --> 08:28.968
The men are down there like lords.

08:30.000 --> 08:31.604
Esme, just...

08:32.960 --> 08:34.485
Get on with it.

08:35.039 --> 08:37.202
I'm bloody five months gone.

08:37.840 --> 08:39.568
(SNIFFING)

08:41.400 --> 08:45.405
-(SIGHS) I forgot the combination.
-24-8-22.

08:46.760 --> 08:48.922
How do you know
the paper cash combination?

08:49.000 --> 08:51.651
- Tommy talks in his sleep.
- Shut up, Esme.

08:52.520 --> 08:53.681
(CLAN KS)

08:54.080 --> 08:55.366
(GROAN5)

08:57.000 --> 08:58.490
He's changed the combination.

09:01.160 --> 09:04.289
- LIZZIE: You've put it in wrong.
- No, I haven't.

09:07.200 --> 09:08.565
Your hands are shaking.

09:09.280 --> 09:10.281
(CREAKS)

09:11.680 --> 09:12.806
(SNIFFING)

09:24.640 --> 09:27.769
And actually, I am sleeping with Tommy,
OK? Now and then.

09:28.120 --> 09:30.566
Because he wants to, now and then.
When the mood takes him.

09:30.960 --> 09:32.041
Except we don't sleep.

09:32.120 --> 09:34.771
It's hard to sleep
bent over a desk, isn't it?

09:36.280 --> 09:37.327
Happy?

09:39.560 --> 09:41.562
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(WOMEN TALKING IN DISTINCTLY)

09:41.640 --> 09:43.802
None of it's fucking fair.

09:47.960 --> 09:49.485
TOMMY: It's two hours' work.

09:49.560 --> 09:51.449
Bit of grease on your cuffs,
and that's it.

09:51.520 --> 09:53.204
Tommy, should I really be here for this?

09:53.280 --> 09:54.964
I've cleared it with Polly.

09:55.040 --> 09:57.520
There's no way around it.
We need you to know.

09:57.600 --> 10:01.286
Who the fuck wants to buy
27 stolen armoured cars?

10:01.360 --> 10:02.566
A foolish man.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.642
MICHAEL: And how much
is this foolish man paying?

10:04.720 --> 10:08.850
£150,000. Cash, diamonds and sapphires.

10:09.960 --> 10:11.849
So that's 20 for you, Charlie.

10:13.360 --> 10:15.408
Isiah, there's 5 to you.

10:15.480 --> 10:18.723
The rest we take to America
to invest in legally-acquired property.

10:19.040 --> 10:21.884
Assets bought
with untraceable income resold,

10:21.960 --> 10:24.361
and the profits reinvested
to make sure it's clean.

10:24.440 --> 10:26.010
ARTHUR: And after that, I suppose,

10:26.080 --> 10:28.970
the whole business
will be like that stag

10:29.040 --> 10:30.929
hanging up over there, right, Tom?

10:31.000 --> 10:32.809
Well, with profits on this scale,

10:32.880 --> 10:35.724
we'll be in a position
to stop the off-track business for good.

10:35.800 --> 10:38.326
Keep the pubs, stop the protection.

10:38.800 --> 10:41.644
Horses for the sport
and race days for a lark.

10:43.240 --> 10:46.369
I made a promise to Charles' mother.

10:46.440 --> 10:49.728
Now, I also made a promise to Linda.

10:51.160 --> 10:52.241
I know.

10:53.080 --> 10:54.923
I can see it in your eyes, man.

10:55.000 --> 10:56.809
Part of the reason
for doing this lastjob

10:56.880 --> 11:00.771
is so you'll be set up
when you do decide to walk away.

11:02.080 --> 11:03.605
CHARLIE: Look at you, Arthur.

11:04.560 --> 11:06.927
A man that wants to live a clean life,

11:07.000 --> 11:10.482
but here you are signing up for
the biggest robbery of all.

11:11.520 --> 11:13.010
I have to hand it to you, Tom.

11:13.440 --> 11:15.966
- You're a smart man.
- You in or out, Charlie?

11:21.760 --> 11:22.841
Curly?

11:23.880 --> 11:25.166
Shouldn't have killed the stag, Tommy.

11:25.240 --> 11:26.810
- Oh, shut up. Shut up.
- Bad luck.

11:28.080 --> 11:31.448
How do we know this foolish man will
hand over the diamonds when we're done?

11:31.520 --> 11:33.090
We don't.

11:33.160 --> 11:34.525
But that's another business.

11:36.400 --> 11:39.563
Right, let's cook some meat.

11:44.360 --> 11:45.964
(BANGING ON DOOR)

11:46.040 --> 11:47.485
ESME: Can't wait to
part with their money,

11:47.560 --> 11:49.005
stupid bastards.

11:49.080 --> 11:50.923
LINDA: It's all right, it's me.

11:54.520 --> 11:55.567
(DOOR CLOSES)

11:55.640 --> 11:59.201
Arthur said you'd be short-staffed today
because they are on a works outing.

11:59.280 --> 12:00.645
ESME: Piss-up, actually.

12:01.680 --> 12:04.809
I brought sandwiches
and the lemonade I made myself.

12:04.880 --> 12:06.006
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

12:06.080 --> 12:09.323
I'll make tea and empty ashtrays,
but I won't handle money or slips.

12:10.880 --> 12:13.804
Arthur says what you do here
is illegal, but not immoral.

12:14.680 --> 12:16.921
ESME: Depends what time
you get here, Linda.

12:17.760 --> 12:19.285
And anyway,

12:19.360 --> 12:22.648
I thought I'd offer you my physical and
spiritual support in your time of need.

12:22.720 --> 12:24.165
Oh, Linda, if you want to be a help,

12:24.240 --> 12:27.369
run up to the shops
and get me 20 Senior Service.

12:27.880 --> 12:30.690
- Lizzie'll give you the change.
-(CHUCKLES) No, I won't.

12:30.760 --> 12:33.411
Actually, I'll use my own money, Polly.

12:34.240 --> 12:37.687
And before you ladies decide to find me
so amusing, I have a message for you.

12:37.760 --> 12:38.807
Oh, God, no, Linda.

12:38.880 --> 12:40.609
I've been to church already. Have you?

12:40.680 --> 12:42.842
It's not a message from God, Polly.

12:42.920 --> 12:45.969
- I1:'s from Jessie Eden.
- Who's Jessie Eden?

12:46.040 --> 12:48.884
LINDA: She's the lady shop steward
at the Lucas factory in Sparkhill.

12:48.960 --> 12:50.291
ESME: Lady shop steward?

12:50.360 --> 12:51.964
She's bringing all the female workers

12:52.040 --> 12:53.804
in the spot-welding
and wire-cutting shops

12:53.880 --> 12:55.006
out on strike for the day.

12:55.280 --> 12:57.965
In protest at being made to work
on a holy day.

12:58.280 --> 13:01.489
Poor conditions, lack of holidays,
unsanitary lavatory provisions

13:01.560 --> 13:03.562
and lower pay for female workers.

13:04.120 --> 13:07.124
Apparently, all the female
factory workers in the city

13:07.200 --> 13:09.168
are joining the protest in sympathy

13:09.400 --> 13:11.641
and will walk out of
their places of work at 9 a.m.

13:11.720 --> 13:14.291
-to march on the Bull Ring.
-(BANGING ON DOOR)

13:14.360 --> 13:17.091
All oppressed female workers welcome.

13:17.160 --> 13:18.924
Them bastards down there shooting deer.

13:19.000 --> 13:21.241
Me five months gone,
sat here like a pudding.

13:21.320 --> 13:23.607
LIZZIE: Only one outside lavatory
between the lot of us.

13:23.680 --> 13:24.841
Not consulted.

13:24.920 --> 13:26.649
- Bent over a fucking desk.
-(BANGING CONTINUES)

13:26.960 --> 13:29.566
Ladies, I honestly believe
those who march on Good Friday

13:29.640 --> 13:31.130
will have God on their side.

13:31.240 --> 13:32.651
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
- MAN: It's 9 o'clock, ladies!

13:32.720 --> 13:34.529
Open the fucking door!

13:36.840 --> 13:38.046
Fuck it.

13:38.920 --> 13:40.968
I'm not in the mood today.

13:44.320 --> 13:46.084
Let's go to the Bull Ring.

13:46.800 --> 13:48.211
Hallelujah!

13:48.280 --> 13:50.408
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

14:25.440 --> 14:27.044
MICHAEL: The foolish man?

14:28.400 --> 14:29.731
Not quite.

14:48.960 --> 14:50.530
I'm sorry I came unannounced.

14:51.160 --> 14:52.207
What do you want?

14:52.800 --> 14:54.325
We need proof.

14:55.200 --> 14:57.282
Proof of what? (CLEARS THROAT)

14:57.360 --> 14:59.362
You said the priest is a traitor.

14:59.680 --> 15:01.284
We need to know how you know.

15:02.320 --> 15:03.685
The proof is my word.

15:05.600 --> 15:08.001
If he is involved, I'm out.
He needs to die.

15:08.600 --> 15:10.250
Are you always so violent?

15:13.200 --> 15:14.725
I killed a stag today,

15:15.680 --> 15:17.284
and it hurt me to do it.

15:18.560 --> 15:20.767
But I treated it with respect,

15:20.840 --> 15:23.127
and the spare meat
will go to poor people.

15:24.920 --> 15:28.845
It will grieve me far less
to put a bullet in the priest's face.

15:31.760 --> 15:34.001
Will you not sit when a duchess sits?

15:35.520 --> 15:38.046
I'm told you're part of the deal.
Is that true?

15:39.200 --> 15:42.363
The Royal Court in Tbilisi
actually worked very efficiently.

15:42.440 --> 15:45.125
Ah, I see. And it worked like this, eh?

15:45.200 --> 15:48.966
TATIANA: There were lots of
corridors and small rooms.

15:49.040 --> 15:50.280
Attics.

15:50.360 --> 15:52.727
There were no rules there.
Deals were done.

15:52.800 --> 15:54.768
Brothers gave sisters,
aunts gave uncles,

15:54.840 --> 15:56.604
fathers gave daughters and servants.

15:56.680 --> 15:57.841
(GLASS CLIN KS)

15:59.480 --> 16:01.847
It was my aunt's idea that I came alone.

16:04.560 --> 16:06.369
She is in charge of this.

16:14.520 --> 16:17.330
When there are no rules,
women take charge.

16:18.000 --> 16:21.482
They understand that the power they have
comes through silent agreements.

16:21.560 --> 16:25.360
I've promised I will do everything I can
to make this plan work.

16:25.440 --> 16:28.330
My aunt assumed you would want me
as part of the deal.

16:30.240 --> 16:31.571
I will tell her she's wrong.

16:31.640 --> 16:33.802
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)
-(DOOR OPENS)

16:34.400 --> 16:37.165
(CHUCKLING) Tommy,
you ain't gonna believe this, man.

16:37.680 --> 16:39.967
I just phoned the garrison, right?
I just spoke to Billy.

16:40.040 --> 16:44.648
He says Polly, Esme and Lizzie have
gone on fucking strike.

16:44.720 --> 16:46.006
(LAUGHS)

16:46.080 --> 16:48.321
- They what?
- They've gone on fucking strike!

16:49.160 --> 16:50.730
Half of Birmingham is out.

16:50.800 --> 16:53.690
The female half, they're all out,
every single one of them.

16:53.760 --> 16:55.046
Quakers put 'em up to it.

16:56.440 --> 16:57.601
Who's watching the shop?

16:58.160 --> 16:59.321
JOHN: Polly's locked it up.

17:00.120 --> 17:02.771
See, Good Friday's
one of our best days for takings.

17:04.200 --> 17:08.090
All the men get drunk.
The races are all fixed.

17:08.160 --> 17:11.130
It's like picking apples
off the lowest branches.

17:11.200 --> 17:12.486
Hey, john?

17:13.000 --> 17:14.080
Hmm, yes.

17:14.400 --> 17:16.128
Then your business is very easy.

17:18.359 --> 17:20.203
- Was Linda with them?
- You know,

17:20.800 --> 17:23.723
Billy said that Pollyjumped
in the fucking Bull Ring,

17:23.800 --> 17:26.770
just pissed out of her mind,
started going on about revolution,

17:26.839 --> 17:28.079
screaming to the rooftops.

17:28.600 --> 17:30.329
Was Linda with them?

17:31.440 --> 17:32.566
Yeah.

17:33.400 --> 17:35.289
Then it was Linda's idea.

17:35.760 --> 17:38.491
- Linda's a smart woman.
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

17:44.800 --> 17:45.961
john.

17:47.120 --> 17:48.849
There's a Bentley in the drive outside.

17:48.920 --> 17:51.048
I want you to go out
and put a nail in its tyre.

17:51.120 --> 17:53.930
It's Good Friday,
so there'll be no garages open.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.604
The lady will have to spend the night.

17:56.040 --> 17:58.361
Then I want you and the boys
to all go home.

17:58.440 --> 18:01.046
You take Charlie, put him with
Arthur and Linda for the night.

18:01.120 --> 18:03.088
They can use the practise.

18:06.280 --> 18:08.203
- You want to put a nail...
- Yeah.

18:08.520 --> 18:10.170
- You heard me.
- Yeah.

18:10.560 --> 18:13.211
Right. Nice to meet you.

18:17.440 --> 18:19.841
Why do you need
to put a nail in the tyre?

18:20.560 --> 18:23.131
I want it so neither of us
can change our minds.

18:30.040 --> 18:31.371
(CREAKING)

18:33.320 --> 18:35.129
(CLANKING)

18:47.080 --> 18:48.684
JOHN: We came back early.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.089
Polly didn't finish the count yesterday.

18:56.920 --> 18:58.046
Hmm.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.564
So you thought you could take a tenner.

19:01.320 --> 19:02.924
I thought I'd finish the count.

19:07.400 --> 19:09.243
(BOTH GRUNTING)

19:10.680 --> 19:11.806
JOHN: Hey!

19:11.880 --> 19:14.486
Esme, I've told you.
Stay off the snow till the baby's born.

19:14.560 --> 19:17.530
ESME: It does no harm, passes the time.

19:17.600 --> 19:20.444
- Knocks down the walls.
- Listen. (GRUNTS)

19:21.600 --> 19:23.250
(PANTING) Listen.

19:24.440 --> 19:26.442
I know you miss the travelling.

19:27.160 --> 19:28.844
It's all gonna be all right.

19:29.800 --> 19:31.768
It's like being a hen in a coop.

19:35.840 --> 19:38.047
Remember that house in Lichfield?

19:39.160 --> 19:41.686
The one the bailiff used to
throw you out of?

19:41.760 --> 19:43.330
