except for one bullet.

23:49.280 --> 23:51.647
- No! No, please.
- This is a game we used to play.

23:52.360 --> 23:53.407
No.

23:54.120 --> 23:56.009
- Watch.
- Do not fucking do this.

23:56.080 --> 23:58.162
No. Look at me.

23:58.840 --> 23:59.887
Don't do this.

23:59.960 --> 24:01.007
_ (CLICKS)
"No!

24:01.080 --> 24:02.969
Give me the fucking thing.

24:05.040 --> 24:07.361
It brings you alive. You won't try it?

24:07.440 --> 24:09.010
No, I do not want to try!

24:09.080 --> 24:12.163
And I do not want
your mad fucking Russian brains

24:12.240 --> 24:14.049
all over me fucking walls.

24:14.120 --> 24:15.884
I survive each time by the will of God.

24:15.960 --> 24:17.325
Get to fucking bed, now!

24:17.400 --> 24:19.209
TATIANA: I already called a maid.

24:19.280 --> 24:20.441
TOMMY: Fucking...

24:33.480 --> 24:34.606
You see?

24:35.560 --> 24:37.210
You are afraid.

24:39.400 --> 24:42.006
Like a boy who's broken in
through the window.

24:43.200 --> 24:45.851
I need to educate you
in how to run a house like this.

24:45.920 --> 24:47.160
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

24:47.680 --> 24:49.125
Yes. Come down.

24:49.640 --> 24:50.687
Pour us a drink.

24:50.800 --> 24:52.882
Mary, go back to bed, please.

24:53.120 --> 24:55.851
You go back to bed, please.
This woman is drunk.

24:56.120 --> 24:57.884
That's all right, sir.
Should I pour whisky?

24:57.960 --> 25:00.440
- Yes, he will have whisky...
- No, go back to bed.

25:00.520 --> 25:02.602
He will have whisky
and I will have wine!

25:03.360 --> 25:04.691
Mary, go back to bed.

25:04.760 --> 25:06.489
- In a house like this...
- TOMMY: Stop talking.

25:06.560 --> 25:08.847
- The servants expect it.
- Go back to bed! Do as I say!

25:08.920 --> 25:10.570
Normally, if there's a call
after midnight,

25:10.640 --> 25:12.688
the maid who comes in
is the one in love with the master,

25:12.760 --> 25:16.606
-but she is not in love with you.
- This is not fucking Russia!

25:16.680 --> 25:19.524
(SOFTLY) Please, Mary.
Go back to bed, hey?

25:33.640 --> 25:35.688
I know your weakness, Tommy.

25:38.440 --> 25:39.885
It's freedom.

25:41.800 --> 25:43.040
Madness.

25:44.320 --> 25:45.651
Killing.

25:50.440 --> 25:55.287
I am the first one who understands you.

26:04.720 --> 26:06.290
(FOOTSTEPS TH U DDING)

26:42.040 --> 26:43.804
I found her perfume.

26:45.280 --> 26:46.611
Put it on.

26:51.160 --> 26:54.323
What proof do you have
that the priest is a spy?

26:54.680 --> 26:57.081
I told you. I gave you my word.

27:15.440 --> 27:16.885
Then kill him.

27:19.920 --> 27:23.402
From now on, you must do
everything that you want to do.

27:52.520 --> 27:54.807
There'll be two of us for breakfast
this morning, Mary.

27:54.880 --> 27:57.326
She's gone for a walk by the river.

27:57.400 --> 27:59.971
- MARY: The lady left, sir.
-(CUTLERY CLIN KS)

28:00.120 --> 28:01.849
Left? How?

28:02.480 --> 28:03.641
She took your car.

28:04.880 --> 28:05.927
She what?

28:06.000 --> 28:09.482
She was in a terrible hurry.
She said she had your permission.

28:10.000 --> 28:13.686
She told David to go to the garage
to get a new tyre for the Bentley.

28:13.760 --> 28:15.410
She said you could use that.

28:16.280 --> 28:18.442
And why the hell
would you listen to her, eh?

28:18.840 --> 28:20.410
The way she said it, sir.

28:53.920 --> 28:55.410
(DOOR CLOSES)

28:55.480 --> 28:58.211
-jOHN: How was she, Tom?
- Talkative, yeah.

28:58.280 --> 28:59.327
Hmm.

28:59.760 --> 29:01.444
I was fucking working, all right?

29:01.800 --> 29:02.847
Yeah.

29:04.720 --> 29:06.927
From what she said,
when she was out of her fucking mind,

29:07.000 --> 29:09.367
I'm pretty certain
the treasury is underneath the house.

29:09.440 --> 29:10.441
What have you got?

29:10.520 --> 29:12.807
Our Ada got this
from the British Library

29:12.880 --> 29:14.928
using her scholar's pass.

29:16.360 --> 29:17.646
She talks about her aunt

29:17.720 --> 29:19.643
coming up the stairs
to have her breakfast in the morning,

29:19.720 --> 29:22.690
which means
it has to be in the building somewhere.

29:22.760 --> 29:25.001
ARTHUR: Wine cellar. Septic.

29:25.480 --> 29:27.164
Kitchen cellar.

29:27.240 --> 29:28.446
And a tunnel under the river.

29:28.520 --> 29:29.965
They don't trust a soul in this country,

29:30.040 --> 29:33.681
so my guess is they've turned
one of the cellars into a strong room.

29:33.760 --> 29:34.841
Did you find someone, Arthur?

29:35.240 --> 29:36.651
Moss gave me this.

29:36.720 --> 29:38.848
Stefan Radischevsky.

29:38.920 --> 29:41.287
He's a kid from Greet,
lives in Cheltenham.

29:41.360 --> 29:45.081
Dad's a Russian. He has dreams of
owning a pub but he's got a record.

29:45.360 --> 29:47.010
- Breaking and entering.
- ARTHUR: Hmm.

29:47.080 --> 29:48.730
- And he speaks Russian?
- Yeah.

29:48.800 --> 29:51.770
Their butler drinks in a pub
called the Masons Arms.

29:51.840 --> 29:53.001
Get to him, tell him who we are,

29:53.080 --> 29:55.970
offer him some money
if he gives the kid a job in the house.

29:56.040 --> 29:57.371
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
- Wait.

29:57.920 --> 29:59.604
Talk to the kid,

29:59.680 --> 30:01.967
offer him one of the pubs
we took off the Italians

30:02.040 --> 30:05.283
if he works in the house for four weeks,
keeps his ears open.

30:05.360 --> 30:06.521
All right?

30:06.600 --> 30:07.761
Come.

30:10.080 --> 30:12.970
The executive committee of
the union of bookies and allied trades

30:13.040 --> 30:14.485
will see you now, sir.

30:24.240 --> 30:25.890
(IN DISTINCT CHATTER)

30:27.680 --> 30:31.048
I heard you were giving speeches
off the back of a wagon, Pol.

30:31.880 --> 30:34.611
I can't remember a fucking thing.

30:34.680 --> 30:38.002
Well, Moss tells me you were threatening
to burn down the town hall.

30:38.320 --> 30:40.800
Oh, Tommy, we were having a laugh.

30:42.120 --> 30:44.487
You know, actually,
the crowd around me was bigger

30:44.560 --> 30:46.244
than the crowd around Jessie Eden.

30:46.320 --> 30:47.526
TOMMY: Who's Jessie Eden?

30:47.600 --> 30:48.761
POLLY: She's too soft.

30:48.840 --> 30:50.763
You're not gonna
break the capitalist system

30:50.840 --> 30:53.525
talking about
separate lavatories for women.

30:53.600 --> 30:54.681
Who is Jessie Eden?

30:55.000 --> 30:56.411
She's our new best friend.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.482
Shop steward at the Lucas factory.

30:58.560 --> 31:00.449
A woman shop steward, I've heard of her.

31:00.520 --> 31:02.682
There is a leaflet here
if you want to take a look, Tommy.

31:04.840 --> 31:06.330
(LIZZIE CLEARS THROAT)

31:07.800 --> 31:10.804
So, a separate lavatory?
Is that it? Is that what you want?

31:11.440 --> 31:12.441
I don't know what you want.

31:12.520 --> 31:15.444
You have to tell me what it is
that you want and then I'll know.

31:15.840 --> 31:19.731
Actually, we want to know
about the robbery you're planning.

31:19.800 --> 31:22.167
Not the factory robbery. The other one.

31:22.800 --> 31:25.041
The one you're not
telling the women about.

31:25.480 --> 31:27.209
- John has a big mouth.
- ESME: No.

31:28.400 --> 31:33.042
Arthur's got a big mouth.
Arthur told Linda, Linda told me.

31:34.800 --> 31:36.404
- Polly?
- Read the leaflet, Tommy.

31:36.480 --> 31:39.370
Ladies, why don't I
talk to Tommy privately,

31:39.440 --> 31:41.681
and then I'll
report back to you faithfully.

31:41.760 --> 31:44.411
You're not just gonna take payment
from the Russians, are you, Tommy?

31:44.800 --> 31:46.802
You're going to clean them out,
is that right?

31:46.880 --> 31:47.961
- LIZZIE: Esme?
- So...

31:48.600 --> 31:51.365
What happens after,
when they come for us?

31:51.440 --> 31:52.851
When I'm about to give birth?

31:52.920 --> 31:55.526
Get out, get back to work.

31:55.600 --> 31:56.806
Esme, come on.

31:59.400 --> 32:02.006
- Keep us posted, won't you, sister?
- I will.

32:03.200 --> 32:04.201
(DOOR CLOSES)

32:06.840 --> 32:07.921
Fucking hell.

32:11.720 --> 32:13.802
So Arthur tells Linda everything, eh?

32:14.240 --> 32:17.369
She's stolen his soul
and taken it to a better place.

32:17.440 --> 32:18.487
The suburbs.

32:18.880 --> 32:21.008
Where men are honest with their wives.

32:22.360 --> 32:23.361
We can trust Lizzie.

32:24.840 --> 32:26.842
Yeah, but I can't trust Esme.

32:27.440 --> 32:29.727
I can't trust the fucking Russians
to pay me or the army,

32:29.800 --> 32:32.565
and I can't trust my own brother
to keep his fucking mouth shut.

32:33.800 --> 32:35.529
Did you make progress last night?

32:39.000 --> 32:40.126
Yes.

32:41.960 --> 32:45.442
John said the girl looks like
Edna Purviance from the pictures.

32:45.960 --> 32:47.849
(CLICKS TONGUE) Be careful.

32:50.880 --> 32:52.644
She's an excellent source of information

32:52.720 --> 32:54.290
regarding the location
of the merchandise.

32:54.360 --> 32:55.361
- Here we go.
- You know,

32:55.440 --> 32:58.444
there is a general lack of discipline
in this fucking company.

33:00.280 --> 33:02.009
She stayed the night.

33:03.400 --> 33:04.811
I'm working, Pol.

33:05.440 --> 33:07.886
I am working for
the good of the company.

33:10.160 --> 33:11.400
You're grieving.

33:12.840 --> 33:14.569
And when you grieve,
you make bad choices.

33:15.120 --> 33:17.885
I know. I did it myself.

33:17.960 --> 33:20.008
Look. No more marches.

33:20.760 --> 33:22.250
No more fucking politics.

33:22.320 --> 33:24.721
It can kill us. All right?
joke or no joke.

33:25.320 --> 33:26.890
Did you tell Arthur about the priest?

33:27.440 --> 33:28.851
I only told you.

33:30.120 --> 33:31.485
Thanks for the burden.

33:33.920 --> 33:35.285
(BELL TOLLING)

33:43.320 --> 33:45.800
You were correct
not to talk over the phone.

33:45.880 --> 33:47.530
What did she say?

33:49.680 --> 33:52.889
She said there was gonna be a killing.
A holy man.

33:54.640 --> 33:57.007
And she was with the Shelbys, was she?

33:57.800 --> 33:59.006
(SIGHS)

34:27.199 --> 34:29.885
I suppose you have something to say
about yesterday.

34:30.520 --> 34:31.760
No.

34:31.840 --> 34:33.489
It's something else, actually.

34:37.199 --> 34:38.440
I believe Arthur has told you

34:38.520 --> 34:40.920
about some business
we're planning, Linda.

34:41.400 --> 34:43.402
Oh, there's always business, Thomas.

34:43.760 --> 34:45.808
And Arthur believes when
this business is done,

34:45.880 --> 34:47.166
it'll all be over.

34:48.560 --> 34:50.801
Arthur believes you, but I don't.

34:52.600 --> 34:53.647
(SIGHS)

34:53.719 --> 34:58.408
Linda, the people who have hired us
to rob the factory are very bad people.

34:59.320 --> 35:01.049
They'll not pay us, as they've promised.

35:01.120 --> 35:05.250
So, on the night of the robbery, we will
take what is ours from their treasury.

35:05.320 --> 35:06.970
And a bit more on top for luck.

35:07.240 --> 35:09.561
If you're saying
you're gonna stop Arthur,

35:09.640 --> 35:10.880
I need to know.

35:11.600 --> 35:13.204
That'll be Arthur's decision.

35:14.440 --> 35:16.761
And your plan is still
to reform him, eh?

35:16.840 --> 35:19.764
- To the absolute degree of redemption.
- Mmm-hmm.

35:21.400 --> 35:25.325
Well, Arthur will walk away from this
with £30,000. We made a deal.

35:25.560 --> 35:26.925
And afterwards,

35:28.000 --> 35:30.685
you and Arthur can begin your new life.

35:35.320 --> 35:37.049
Did you say 30,000?

35:38.200 --> 35:41.522
Arthur said the estimated total proceeds
would be 150,000.

35:41.600 --> 35:43.921
- Estimated. Yes.
- A third of 150 is 50.

35:44.000 --> 35:45.365
- Why a third?
- The three brothers.

35:45.440 --> 35:47.010
- Finn is not yet a man.
- There are expenses.

35:47.080 --> 35:48.411
Of 25,000, you said.

35:48.560 --> 35:50.403
As of last night,
the expenses increased.

35:50.480 --> 35:51.845
We need to dig a hole.

35:51.920 --> 35:53.922
Arthur agreed to a plan
with a figure of 25.

35:55.520 --> 35:58.205
25 from 150 is 125.

35:58.280 --> 36:01.363
A third of that is £41,000.

36:02.880 --> 36:04.006
(scoffs)

36:05.360 --> 36:06.441
Sugar?

36:07.080 --> 36:08.081
Yes.

36:11.120 --> 36:12.884
(CROCKERY CLIN KING)

36:14.440 --> 36:15.771
Thank you.

36:17.560 --> 36:19.210
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

36:23.520 --> 36:26.046
So, you've worked this all out, I see?

36:26.640 --> 36:29.246
Only in my head.
I haven't written it down.

36:31.040 --> 36:33.247
Linda, are you saying...

36:35.920 --> 36:37.684
If it were 41,000".

36:37.760 --> 36:41.242
I've already told you,
that'll be Arthur's decision.

36:42.600 --> 36:45.365
But I don't imagine
he'll accept less than 41.

36:48.520 --> 36:50.249
- May I smoke?
- No.

36:57.520 --> 36:59.249
So, I imagine you have some plans

37:00.800 --> 37:02.290
for your 41,000.

37:03.320 --> 37:05.641
Yes. California.

37:06.400 --> 37:08.641
For the child's health,
away from the smoke.

37:09.160 --> 37:11.731
We want to run a general store
on an Indian mission.

37:12.360 --> 37:15.489
The Americans invite Quakers
to do good work with the Indians.

37:16.720 --> 37:19.041
We've already sent our papers
and been accepted.

37:20.320 --> 37:21.765
(CHUCKLES)

37:21.840 --> 37:23.888
Arthur Shelby as a missionary...

37:23.960 --> 37:27.282
- No. Arthur will run the store.
- Hmm.

37:28.000 --> 37:29.889
I will teach in the school next to it.

37:31.040 --> 37:34.840
Arthur will swim in the ocean.
I will be on the beach with a towel.

37:34.920 --> 37:35.967
The open air and the sun

37:36.040 --> 37:38.361
will get rid of all the nonsense
in his head from France.

37:42.280 --> 37:43.770
That's some plan.

37:44.680 --> 37:46.250
As you know yourself,

37:47.680 --> 37:48.681
the arrival of a new life

37:48.760 --> 37:51.161
concentrates the mind
on practical things.

37:51.640 --> 37:53.085
Amen to that.

37:56.520 --> 37:57.726
When is the child due?

37:58.000 --> 37:59.240
September.

37:59.800 --> 38:00.926
When is the robbery?

38:02.160 --> 38:03.286
June.

38:04.880 --> 38:06.769
Then the timing's perfect.

38:08.760 --> 38:10.444
We'll book a passage
through the Panama Canal

38:10.520 --> 38:13.410
the day after
the 41,000 is paid to Arthur.

38:13.480 --> 38:14.686
(coucamwe)

38:16.280 --> 38:18.647
Did we agree 41,000, Linda?

38:19.600 --> 38:21.250
I heard nothing to the contrary.

38:24.080 --> 38:27.050
- RUBEN: Word association. Right now.
- Oh, God. I hate this game.

38:27.120 --> 38:28.565
It's Freud. It's terribly fashionable.

38:28.640 --> 38:31.211
I'd rather you put on
that music that I hate.

38:31.280 --> 38:33.886
(SIGHS) Are we going mad
in here, do you think?

38:33.960 --> 38:35.007
Yes.

38:35.240 --> 38:37.891
(CHUCKLES) We shouldn't have drunk
red wine with the cake.

38:38.360 --> 38:42.160
And I believe your vow never to sleep
with another man is a good one.

38:42.800 --> 38:44.086
Good for the painting.

38:45.120 --> 38:47.088
It's not a vow. It's just...

38:48.280 --> 38:51.727
I think when men want sex,
they become hilarious.

38:52.840 --> 38:57.482
Like a dog, when you pick up a lead,
and he knows he's going for a walk.

39:02.480 --> 39:04.801
May I respectfully point out

39:05.200 --> 39:09.683
that so far you haven't even
picked up the bloody lead.

39:14.960 --> 39:16.007
There.

39:18.880 --> 39:20.041
That's the look.

39:20.720 --> 39:21.926
Imperious.

39:23.600 --> 39:26.080
No man is good enough.

39:46.280 --> 39:48.362
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

39:51.680 --> 39:53.603
-(ROARS)
-(ALL SCREAMING)

39:57.360 --> 39:58.964
(IN DISTINCT CHATTER)

40:34.760 --> 40:36.444
(WATER DRIPPING)

41:01.880 --> 41:03.325
(GRUNTING)

41:32.800 --> 41:34.290
(BOTH GRUNTING)

41:36.480 --> 41:38.084
(SCREAMING)

41:40.240 --> 41:41.401
(CRACK)

41:42.800 --> 41:43.801
(THUD)

41:46.840 --> 41:48.330
(ENGINE IDLING)

42:05.600 --> 42:07.284
(IN HALES SHARPLY)

42:30.440 --> 42:32.920
PATRICK: You idiot.
You nearly killed him.

42:33.000 --> 42:35.480
I told you we needed him
fully conscious.

42:36.160 --> 42:39.881
We need to stop using soldiers
who've been in India, they hit too hard.

42:39.960 --> 42:41.450
HUGHES: Not fucking hard enough.

42:41.520 --> 42:43.329
Hey, Mr Shelby. Hey.

42:43.400 --> 42:46.244
I heard about your plan
to kill a holy man

42:46.320 --> 42:48.561
from a voice in the confessional.

42:48.640 --> 42:49.801
PATRICK: Can you hear us?

42:49.880 --> 42:51.086
(GROAN5)

42:51.280 --> 42:52.327
Grace?

42:52.760 --> 42:53.966
Shelby.

42:55.600 --> 42:57.887
Why were you attempting
to kill Father Hughes?

43:00.040 --> 43:02.691
Maybe we should wait
until he is fully conscious.

43:02.760 --> 43:04.410
I have a dinner appointment.

43:05.080 --> 43:06.809
Hey, Shelby?

43:07.200 --> 43:09.009
Wake up. Eyes front.

43:09.080 --> 43:10.206
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

43:10.280 --> 43:12.931
Mr Shelby, you were trying to kill me,
were you?

43:14.840 --> 43:16.285
Passing information...

43:17.080 --> 43:18.923
PATRICK: Fuck. He knows.

43:24.160 --> 43:25.321
Where am I?

43:26.080 --> 43:30.165
You are among the Odd Fellows.
Please count from 10 to one.

43:30.640 --> 43:31.971
Ah, fuck you.

43:54.840 --> 43:59.209
Whatever else you might have forgotten
about last night,

43:59.960 --> 44:01.086
remember this.

44:02.520 --> 44:05.330
I am passing on information
to the Soviet Embassy

44:05.840 --> 44:07.569
on the instruction of Section D.

44:08.760 --> 44:10.967
It's part of a bigger picture.

44:11.400 --> 44:15.803
You explain to the Russians
that you were mistaken about me,

44:16.080 --> 44:18.924
and you apologise to me
in front of them.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.844
A threat on your sister
was evidently not enough.

44:25.280 --> 44:28.807
You do as we say,
or we will take your son.

44:29.760 --> 44:33.367
Hear this. We will take your son.

44:33.960 --> 44:35.803
We can do it at any moment.

44:36.400 --> 44:38.880
We have people in your life.

44:43.000 --> 44:46.129
You will make your apology to me
tomorrow night,

44:47.520 --> 44:50.171
and you will repair the damage
you've done.

44:51.040 --> 44:53.520
(ECHOING) Or you will never
see your son again.

45:06.120 --> 45:07.326
(GROANING)

45:19.400 --> 45:20.890
(DOOR OPENS)

45:20.960 --> 45:22.610
MARY: Sir, I don't understand...

45:22.680 --> 45:24.409
(TOMMY PANTING)

45:24.480 --> 45:27.882
I don't understand why,
as a former soldier yourself,

45:27.960 --> 45:30.725
you have sacked all of the former
soldiers on the staff.

45:30.800 --> 45:32.802
It means there is only one man
left in the household.

45:32.880 --> 45:35.850
Mary, I want it so that
Charles is never left on his own.

45:35.920 --> 45:37.001
Understood?

45:38.120 --> 45:39.963
Sir, I should call a doctor.

45:40.040 --> 45:42.611
There will be some men
coming down from Birmingham.

45:42.960 --> 45:44.564
And you put them up here in the house.

45:44.640 --> 45:47.450
You put them in the front and back of
the house, you feed them, and you...

45:47.560 --> 45:49.483
Why are they needed, sir?

45:49.560 --> 45:52.484
I brought a cursed sapphire
into this house, Mary.

45:53.160 --> 45:54.844
And now, I'm paying for it.

45:57.600 --> 45:59.602
And I don't know what to expect.

46:00.600 --> 46:02.648
But neither do my enemies.

46:03.160 --> 46:05.845
Tell David to bring the car around.
I'm going to go to London.

46:06.200 --> 46:08.771
- Sir...
- And get me some tea, Mary.

46:11.280 --> 46:12.566
Yes, sir.

46:13.720 --> 46:14.721
(DOOR OPENS)

46:36.880 --> 46:37.927
ARTHUR: (ON PHONE) <i>Hello?</i>

46:38.000 --> 46:39.604
- Yes, Arthur.
- Tommy?

46:41.160 --> 46:44.642
They want the robbery to be sabotaged.

46:45.160 --> 46:46.889
They don't give a fuck who gets hurt.

46:46.960 --> 46:48.007
<i>Are you OK, Tommy?</i>

46:48.080 --> 46:50.082
- It's a bigger picture now.
<i>- Whaz'...</i>

46:50.920 --> 46:52.081
Did john make a list?

46:52.160 --> 46:53.650
<i>Speak clearer, Tom.</i>

46:53.720 --> 46:54.960
I said did john make a list?

46:55.040 --> 46:57.042
<i>John-Boy] 10/, n!</i>

46:57.120 --> 46:58.201
Right.

46:58.520 --> 47:01.808
<i>Gypsies and kin only. Yeah.</i>

47:01.880 --> 47:03.041
Good.

47:03.800 --> 47:06.007
<i>Tommy, can I ask you why?</i>

47:06.080 --> 47:07.161
<i>Tommy?</i>

47:09.640 --> 47:11.165
(PHONE RINGING)

47:11.240 --> 47:13.971
ADA: No, Karl. I told you.
Go on and play in there.

47:17.400 --> 47:18.447
Hello?

47:19.920 --> 47:23.811
(SIGHS) Ada, it's me. It's Tommy.

47:25.200 --> 47:26.611
Ada, I need you to...

47:27.360 --> 47:30.170
I need you to speak
to one of your comrades

47:30.240 --> 47:33.642
and get me a meeting
with someone from the Soviet Embassy.

47:34.920 --> 47:36.160
Tonight.

47:36.480 --> 47:38.482
Your place, 10 p.m.

47:43.480 --> 47:44.970
(RETCHING)

47:47.880 --> 47:50.121
It seems that Mr Shelby

47:50.200 --> 47:52.646
was given bad information
by an informant

47:53.120 --> 47:55.566
who was also in contact
with the underwriter,

47:56.760 --> 48:00.048
who, as we know,
is in the pocket of the Soviets.

48:01.800 --> 48:04.246
- Wine, Tatiana?
- A little.

48:06.960 --> 48:08.291
Bad girl.

48:11.880 --> 48:13.530
(SNIFFING)

48:29.920 --> 48:31.365
(DOOR OPENS)

48:35.040 --> 48:36.201
(DOOR CLOSES)

48:39.280 --> 48:40.725
(SNIFFS)

48:40.800 --> 48:42.609
Sorry I'm late. I, uh...

48:45.720 --> 48:48.610
There was a body on the line.
(CLEARS THROAT)

48:49.000 --> 48:50.286
Drink, Mr Shelby?

48:51.200 --> 48:52.406
No, thank you.

48:52.480 --> 48:54.164
It was drink that caused
half this trouble.

48:55.200 --> 48:57.771
I have come here to apologise.

48:59.120 --> 49:01.646
I have already explained
that you now realise

49:01.720 --> 49:06.282
that your absurd allegation against me
was false.

49:07.160 --> 49:08.321
Indeed.

49:08.720 --> 49:11.644
HUGHES: And that your base nature
made you rash.

49:12.040 --> 49:13.246
(SNIFFS)

49:14.200 --> 49:17.682
And that now, once again,
our plan is back on track.

49:19.080 --> 49:22.050
When a child in my care commits a sin,

49:23.560 --> 49:26.450
first of all, he confesses,
as you just did.

49:26.920 --> 49:29.810
And then,
I instruct him to perform penance

49:30.480 --> 49:32.403
in a manner of my choosing.

49:32.880 --> 49:34.484
As a child, you went to church?

49:35.120 --> 49:36.201
Yes.

49:36.680 --> 49:38.648
HUGHES: Do you remember
the Act of Contrition?

49:40.480 --> 49:41.766
Good.

49:41.840 --> 49:43.683
Do you remember
the words of the Act of Contrition?

49:45.520 --> 49:46.726
(CLEARS THROAT) Yes.

49:49.320 --> 49:52.449
As your penance,
I would like you to recite it now,

49:53.560 --> 49:55.562
in the presence of our associates.

49:57.480 --> 49:58.686
(DOOR OPENS)

50:00.960 --> 50:02.291
Go away.

50:04.360 --> 50:05.691
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

50:06.640 --> 50:07.641
(DOOR CLOSES)

50:08.280 --> 50:09.486
Uh...

50:14.000 --> 50:17.322
Oh, my God,
I am heartily sorry for having...

50:17.400 --> 50:19.607
HUGHES: Instead of "God," say my name.

50:20.360 --> 50:23.330
Since it was me you offended
with your false allegation.

50:27.200 --> 50:30.682
Father Hughes, I am heartily sorry
for having offended you,

50:34.280 --> 50:35.566
because of yourjust punishment,

50:35.640 --> 50:37.483
but most of all,
because they offend you.

50:40.320 --> 50:44.086
Father Hughes, who art all good
and deserving of my love,

50:44.800 --> 50:45.926
(SIGHS)

50:46.920 --> 50:48.524
I firmly resolve to...

50:50.960 --> 50:53.201
With the help of your grace,
to sin no more

50:53.280 --> 50:56.284
and to avoid all near occasions of sin.

50:57.560 --> 50:58.641
Mmm.

51:01.360 --> 51:04.125
Very good. Thank you.

51:05.160 --> 51:06.321
Amen.

51:09.640 --> 51:10.721
(SIGHS)

51:13.080 --> 51:17.165
And now that we are
a united band once more,

51:17.240 --> 51:19.163
perhaps we could order some food.

51:20.400 --> 51:23.244
I'm sorry. I am not feeling well.
I have to go. Good night.

51:24.800 --> 51:26.131
Mr Shelby...

51:32.840 --> 51:34.126
(SNIFFING)

51:35.080 --> 51:36.081
My God, Tommy.

51:36.160 --> 51:37.207
- Are they here?
- Yeah.

51:37.640 --> 51:39.688
- Do you have cocaine?
- No.

51:39.760 --> 51:41.444
-(SIGHS)
- Tommy.

51:44.440 --> 51:47.205
Tommy, this is the Special Adviser
to the Soviet Consul.

51:55.360 --> 51:59.570
Members of the British establishment
and exiled White Russians

51:59.640 --> 52:03.486
are planning to rob armoured cars
from a factory in Birmingham.

52:03.600 --> 52:06.126
We know about the robbery.
We have an informant.

52:06.200 --> 52:10.205
No, your informant is working for them.
They want you to know about the robbery.

52:11.840 --> 52:12.921
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:17.960 --> 52:20.566
Your informant
is working to their instruction.

52:21.840 --> 52:23.171
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:27.000 --> 52:28.923
Why would they want us to know?

52:29.000 --> 52:30.331
They want you to...

52:31.160 --> 52:33.162
They want you to stop the robbery.

52:33.240 --> 52:36.562
They want you to commit a violent act
on British soil.

52:36.640 --> 52:37.801
Tommy, do you want water?

52:38.240 --> 52:39.685
A violent act on British...

52:40.840 --> 52:42.046
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:44.160 --> 52:45.321
(SIGHS)

52:46.720 --> 52:50.202
To force the British government
to break off diplomatic relations.

52:50.520 --> 52:52.045
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:54.360 --> 52:56.044
(SNIFFS) That's the game.

52:57.560 --> 52:59.449
The robbery in Birmingham
is just the bait.

52:59.880 --> 53:01.291
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

53:03.920 --> 53:05.763
Why are you telling us this?

53:06.600 --> 53:09.251
Because my family are the ones
who will be sacrificed

53:10.280 --> 53:12.123
if you decide to blow up the train.

53:12.520 --> 53:13.760
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

53:18.760 --> 53:21.206
The Consul wants to know who you are.

53:22.440 --> 53:23.726
He's Tommy Shelby.

53:24.080 --> 53:25.969
You can take his word.

53:26.040 --> 53:27.610
- Ada.
- Tommy...

53:27.680 --> 53:28.806
Ada.

53:29.200 --> 53:30.281
OK.

53:30.600 --> 53:32.170
(ADA GRUNTING)

53:36.120 --> 53:37.565
Stop, stop.

53:37.640 --> 53:39.449
Ada, stop.

53:39.800 --> 53:41.882
(GRUNTS) 0l<.

53:44.800 --> 53:46.370
Drive me to a hospital, Ada.

53:47.640 --> 53:51.247
If I'm not conscious when I get there,
tell them I have a fractured skull,

53:51.320 --> 53:52.970
concussion and internal bleeding.

53:53.440 --> 53:54.885
I think I may have haemorrhaged.

53:54.960 --> 53:56.325
- Tommy.
- Ada, go on.

53:56.400 --> 53:57.731
- Be quick because I can't see.
- OK.

53:57.800 --> 53:59.211
I can't fucking see.

54:00.280 --> 54:01.964
(SOBS)OK.OK.

54:10.320 --> 54:12.084
Except for you, Dad.

54:16.960 --> 54:18.450
I can see you.

54:36.520 --> 54:38.522
(THEME SONG PLAYING)
